123 or right of way, proposed to be deannexed, containing a complete description of the lands
124 to be deannexed; provided, however, that no more than ten parcels of property may be
125 deannexed in one action and only upon the adoption of a resolution by the governing
126 authority of the county in which such property is located consenting to such deannexation.
127 If the governing authority of the county consents to the deannexation and the deannexation
128 conforms with the requirements of this article, the governing authority of the municipal
129 corporation shall approve such deannexation unless it finds that the deannexation would
130 be detrimental to the health, safety, and welfare of the residents and property owners of the
131 area to be deannexed or to the area remaining within the municipality. If the county is the
132 owner of all parcels proposed for deannexation and the governing authority of the county
133 consents, the governing authority of the municipal corporation shall approve such
134 deannexation within 90 days of the date of the filing of a deannexation application unless
135 it finds that the deannexation would be detrimental to the health, safety, and welfare of the
136 residents and property owners of the area to be deannexed or to the area remaining within
137 the municipality."
138 SECTION 4.
139 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
140 without such approval.
141 SECTION 5.
142 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
